  <section class="docs-block">
    <h3 class="docs-heading">// WHAT IT DOES</h3>
    <p>An AI voice receptionist answers every inbound call in natural conversation, turns it into a booked, rescheduled, or cancelled appointment on a real calendar, and logs the outcome -- without anyone lifting a finger.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-block">
    <h3 class="docs-heading">// HOW IT WORKS</h3>
    <p>It identifies who is calling, answers questions about services, pricing, and hours from a fixed knowledge base, and reads every booking back to confirm before committing it. When the call ends, the transcript, outcome, and recording are saved automatically against the caller's record.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-block">
    <h3 class="docs-heading">// GOOD TO KNOW</h3>
    <p>A work in progress, shown on a fictional business (GreenScape Landscaping). The agent is not on a public line -- live calls are costly to run, so the project is presented here rather than dialled live.</p>
  </section>

</div>
